<h1>String Theory Reading Group</h1>

<h2>January - June '15</h2>

<p>The material discussed will roughly revolve around material presented in Polchinski: bosonic strings, conformal field theory, loop amplitudes, D-branes etc. We will highlight other references when we find Polchinski's treatment too terse.</p>

<p>Each meeting will go on for an hour and a half. We meet every Thursday at 6:00 PM in Hall 123.</p>

<p>Note: An asterisk (*) next to a reference means it was mentioned in passing and is only tangentially related to the material discussed in the talk.</p>

